WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.200
[Amit Varma]: Before we move on with this episode of the Scene in the Unseen, do check out another

00:00:09.200 --> 00:00:18.560
[Amit Varma]: awesome podcast from IVM Podcast, Cyrus Says, hosted by my old buddy, Cyrus Brocha.

00:00:18.560 --> 00:00:22.960
[Amit Varma]: One of the things that most irritates me about political punditry in India is when people

00:00:22.960 --> 00:00:25.680
[Amit Varma]: talk of our politics in terms of left wing and right wing.

00:00:25.680 --> 00:00:29.820
[Amit Varma]: The thing is, this whole construct of left wing and right wing parties is a concept imported

00:00:29.820 --> 00:00:32.840
[Amit Varma]: from the West and doesn't really apply to India.

00:00:32.840 --> 00:00:37.720
[Amit Varma]: The truth is, all our parties are pretty much alike on the left-right spectrum.

00:00:37.720 --> 00:00:43.080
[Amit Varma]: Every party is left-wing on economics, including the BJP, which despite its recent rhetoric,

00:00:43.080 --> 00:00:48.240
[Amit Varma]: believes in a big role for the state and may be pro-business, but it is certainly not pro-markets.

00:00:48.240 --> 00:00:53.000
[Amit Varma]: In fact, between 2014 and 2019, there was nothing in Narendra Modi's economic management

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:57.280
[Amit Varma]: that was different from what Manmohan Singh would have done if in power, except perhaps

00:00:57.280 --> 00:01:01.040
[Amit Varma]: for demonetization, which was reminiscent of Indira Gandhi.

00:01:01.040 --> 00:01:06.440
[Amit Varma]: Arun Shourie famously called the Modi government as UPA plus cow, but even cow is not really

00:01:06.440 --> 00:01:11.560
[Amit Varma]: a differentiator, as the Congress resorted to soft Hindutva during his recent campaign

00:01:11.560 --> 00:01:15.880
[Amit Varma]: and includes welfare schemes for cows in some of the states where it is in charge.

00:01:15.880 --> 00:01:20.120
[Amit Varma]: In other words, all our political parties are left-wing on economics and right-wing

00:01:20.120 --> 00:01:25.720
[Amit Varma]: on social issues, and therefore against individual freedom in every domain, much to the dismay

00:01:25.720 --> 00:01:29.000
[Amit Varma]: of those like me who believe in individual rights.

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:32.360
[Amit Varma]: It is clear that much of our politics is based around identity.

00:01:32.360 --> 00:01:37.080
[Amit Varma]: It is also clear that much of our politics is based around patronage and the bribery

00:01:37.080 --> 00:01:39.680
[Amit Varma]: of voters, direct or indirect.

00:01:39.680 --> 00:01:44.540
[Amit Varma]: Does this mean that ideology does not play a part in Indian politics?

00:01:44.540 --> 00:01:49.360
[Amit Varma]: That is a conventional wisdom, and it is one that we shall examine critically in this episode

00:01:49.360 --> 00:01:52.360
[Amit Varma]: of the Scene and the Unseen.

